<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <script src="https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?v=3.exp"></script>
    <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Marcellus+SC' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>

    <title>Sunset Somewhere</title>
    <link href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lobster' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all' %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag 'application' %>
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    <%= analytics_init if Rails.env.production? %>
    <style type="text/css" media="screen">
      body { 
        background: url("<%= @photo.sunset_by_lat_lon %>") no-repeat center center fixed; 
        -webkit-background-size: cover;
        -moz-background-size: cover;
        -o-background-size: cover;
        background-size: cover;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>

  <div id="city" >
    <p id="city-text" class="alignleft"><a target="_map" href="http://www.openstreetmap.org/?mlat=<%= @photo.lat %>&mlon=<%= @photo.lon %>#map=4/<%= @photo.lat %>/<%= @photo.lon %>"> <%= @photo.location.titleize %>
       <%= image_tag "map_icon.svg", height: '20', width: '20' %></a></p>
  </div>
  <div id="city">
    <p id="attribution-text" class="alignleft"> photo by <a href ="<%=@photo.photo_url%>"><%= @photo.author %></a> on <a href="http://flickr.com">Flickr</a></p>
    <p id="about-text" class="text-muted alignright"><a href="#about" role="button" class="btn" data-toggle="modal">About Sunset Somewhere</a></p>
  </div>


  <div class="modal fade" id="about" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span><span class="sr-only">Close</span></button>
        <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">About Sunset Somewhere</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>Sunset Somewhere lets you follow the <a href="http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/sunearth.html">sliver of the Earth</a> that's moving from day to night. You'll see a photo from somewhere in the world where the sun is setting right now and to see a different view of where the day is ending, just refresh.</p>

        <p><b>A little about how:</b></p>
        <p>To chase the sun as it moves across the earth, every few days we get the sunset time from a sampling of locations around the world. Then we pull photos tagged 'sunset' from <a href="http://flickr.com">Flickr</a> at those locations and add a little extra refining to the photos we pull just to make sure we get great images. Sometimes you'll see a few from the same place, and sometimes you'll hop around the earth a bit. </p>

        <p><i>Created by <a href="https://github.com/mmlkrx" target="_blank">Matthias Loker</a>, <a href="https://github.com/amyrjohnson" target="_blank">Amy Johnson</a> and <a href="https://github.com/zacksheppard" target="_blank">Zack Sheppard</a>.</i></p>

        <p>Location pin icon by <a href="http://www.thenounproject.com/skatakila">Ricardo Moreira</a> from the <a href="http://www.thenounproject.com">Noun Project</a>.</p>
      </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>